<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8334271>
    dc:description "FIGURE 3. Living specimens of Falconina gracilis (Keyserling, 1891) from Goiânia, Goiás, Brazil: A male (MPEG 37222); B female (MPEG 37222). Photos by A. Anker." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8334271/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8334275>
    dc:description "FIGURE 5. Scanning electron microscopy, Falconina gracilis (Keyserling, 1891), left male palp (IBSP 169327):A ventral view; B retrolateral view; C apex of palp, embolus and conductor details, ventral view. Abbreviations AS, apical spur; C, conductor; CRP, cymbial retrolateral basal process; dVL, dorsal lobe of the ventral lobe of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; E, embolus; EP, embolar process; DL, dorsal lobe of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; ML, median lobe of the retrolateral tibial apophysis; T, Tegulum; TP, tegular process; VL, ventral lobe of the retrolateral tibial apophysis. Scale bar A–B. 500 μm; C. 400 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8334275/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8334277>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Scanning electron microscopy, Falconina gracilis (Keyserling, 1891), female genitalia, digested (IBSP 72914): A ventral view; B posterior margin of the epigynal plate and copulatory opening; C dorsal view. D same, primary and secondary spermathecae details. Abbreviations CO, Copulatory opening; FD, fertilization ducts; MnEP, Median notch of the posterior margin of epigynal plate; PVP, posterior vulvar plate; S1, primary spermathecae; S2, secondary spermathecae. Scale bar A–C, 300 μm; B–D 100 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8334277/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8334281>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. A–C. Living female of Falconina gracilis (Keyserling, 1891) (MPEG 37220) from Parque Nacional das Emas, Mineiros, Goiás, Brazil, predating on Atta sp. (Formicidae). Photos by A. Anker." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8334281/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8334285>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Falconina gracilis (Keyserling, 1891), A, C, E, female (IBSP 72914), B, D, F, male (IBSP 169327), G, H Falconina gracilis female holotype (NMH1890.7.1 1243): A–B dorsal habitus; C–D carapace anterior view; E female genitalia ventral view; F male palp, ventral and retrolateral view; G, female genitalia ventral view; G original label." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8334285/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.8334321>
    dc:description "FIGURE 25. Known geographical distribution of Falconina gracilis (Keyserling, 1891). White star represents the type locality of the senior synonym. Blue stars represent the type localities of the junior synonyms. Blue circles represent new records. Green circles represent previous records." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/8334321/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

